.TH "pci_epc_mem_get_order" 9 "pci_epc_mem_get_order" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epc_mem_get_order \- determine the allocation order of a memory size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_epc_mem_get_order
.BI "(struct pci_epc_mem *mem "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mem" 12
address space of the endpoint controller
.IP "size" 12
the size for which to get the order
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reimplement \fBget_order\fP for mem->page_size since the generic get_order
always gets order with a constant PAGE_SIZE.
